JOHANNESBURG - Justin Bieber  is bringing his Purpose tour to South Africa in May. It was announced on Thursday that he will perform in Cape Town on 14 May and Johannesburg on 17 May. Tickets go on sale on Thursday next week, 15 December, at 9am. The Sorry hitmaker has been playing sold-out venues across Europe and America. Global superstar Justin Bieber announced today that his Purpose World Tour will be coming to South Africa in 2017. Presented by Discovery. With worldwide album sales in excess of 100 million units, Bieber has dominated pop culture and social media. His latest album, Purpose, has sold 3.1 million sales worldwide, breaking box office records. The singles What Do you Mean, Sorry and Love Yourself went to number one on the Billboard Top 200, making Bieber the first male artist in almost a decade to have three number ones from an album. eNCA